        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "&c. — In hopeless and remediless calamities. Thus greatly may good men be afflicted, and such dismal apprehensions may they have concerning their afflictions, and such dark conclusions may they sometimes be ready to make concerning the issue of them, through the power of melancholy, and the weakness of faith. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Thy wrath lieth hard upon me — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "The sense of thy wrath, or rather, the effects of it, as the next clause explains it. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Thou hast afflicted me with all thy waves — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "With thy judgments breaking in furiously upon me, like the waves of the sea.",
        "children": []
